England reached 48-0 at stumps on day
two of the second cricket Test against South Africa and trails
by 371 runs.  Captain  Andrew Strauss  has 19 and  Alastair Cook  is on 20 at
Headingley, Leeds.  Earlier, the visitors were all out for 419, having resumed
on 262-5 today after being put in to bat. Alviro Petersen scored
182 before he was caught behind off the bowling of  Stuart Broad .  JP Duminy was 48 not out after captain Graeme Smith scored
52 and AB de Villiers 47. Broad had 3-96, while Steven Finn and
James Anderson each took two wickets.  Play ended early at about 5:15 p.m. because of bad light.  England trails 1-0 in the three-game contest. South Africa
can replace the hosts at the top of the International Cricket
Council Test rankings by winning the series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
